retroarch-appletv4k changelog

2026-04-01  Ryan Musante

	Tagged as v2.15

	* Audit corrections (hardware spec verification + libretro source check)
	* README.md: Appendix A hardware comparison: GPU "4-core" → "5-core"
	  (Apple TV 4K 3rd Gen has the 5-core GPU variant of A15; confirmed
	  Wikipedia, The Apple Wiki, EveryMac)
	* README.md: §7 Latency: Preemptive Frames "v1.16.0+" → "v1.15.0+"
	  (feature debuted in RetroArch v1.15.0, March 2023)
	* README.md: §6 Controllers: DualSense "BT 5.1 low latency" →
	  "BT 5.1 (link limited to Apple TV's BT 5.0)" (Apple TV is BT 5.0;
	  connection negotiates to lower common version)
	* README.md: §11 Known Issues #4: iCloud Sync crash status "Reports" →
	  "Community reports"; expand workaround
	* README.md: Bump version 2.14 → 2.15, rev.13 → rev.14
	* retroarch.cfg: Preemptive Frames comment "v1.16.0+" → "v1.15.0+"
	* retroarch.cfg: Sync source reference to rev.14
	* Add MIT LICENSE file (referenced by README but missing from archive)

2026-04-01  Ryan Musante

	Tagged as v2.14

	* Apply optimization spec v6 (frame pacing, latency stack, per-core audit)
	* retroarch.cfg: Remove video_frame_rest (removed in v1.20.0, obsoleted
	  by frame delay refactor)
	* retroarch.cfg: vrr_runloop_enable "true" → "false" (Apple TV is fixed
	  60 Hz; ON disables DRC, causing judder and audio desync)
	* retroarch.cfg: video_swap_interval "0" → "1" (explicit 60 Hz; auto
	  has documented mis-detection failure modes #15320, #15804)
	* retroarch.cfg: Add video_refresh_rate="59.950001" (calibrated DRC
	  target; recalibrate on device for accuracy)
	* retroarch.cfg: Add audio_max_timing_skew="0.050000" (maximum DRC
	  speed adjustment for core-vs-display rate mismatch)
	* retroarch.cfg: Add cloud_sync_enable_thumbnails="false",
	  cloud_sync_enable_system="false" (exclude large/replaceable data
	  from iCloud sync)
	* retroarch.cfg: Add savestate_thumbnail_enable="true" (v1.21.0+
	  visual save state slot previews)
	* retroarch.cfg: Active keys 41 → 45 (−1 removed, +5 added, 2 modified)
	* retroarch.cfg: Rewind comment: "per-core for Tier 1" → "per-game only"
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: Tier 1 header "rewind + run-ahead safe" →
	  "run-ahead safe"; remove rewind="true" from Mesen, Snes9x, mGBA,
	  Genesis Plus GX, Beetle PCE
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: Snes9x add snes9x_overclock=200 per-game
	  for SuperFX titles
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: Genesis Plus GX add genesis_plus_gx_bram=
	  "per game" for Sega CD save isolation
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: PCSX ReARMed add preemptive="false",
	  video_threaded="true", audio="48", pcsx_rearmed_drc=disabled,
	  pcsx_rearmed_duping_enable=enabled
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: Mupen64Plus-Next add video_threaded="true",
	  EnableCopyColorFromRDRAM=Off, EnableCopyDepthToRDRAM=Software,
	  txFilterMode=None
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: melonDS DS run_ahead "1" → "0"; add
	  preemptive="false", frame_delay_auto="false", video_threaded="true",
	  audio="48", melonds_ds_jit_enable=disabled,
	  melonds_ds_boot_directly=enabled
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: Beetle Saturn add frame_delay_auto="false",
	  video_threaded="true", audio="64", beetle_saturn_cdimagecache=enabled,
	  beetle_saturn_midsync=disabled
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: PPSSPP add frame_delay_auto="false",
	  video_threaded="true", audio="64",
	  ppsspp_texture_scaling_level=1; ppsspp_fast_memory "enabled" →
	  "disabled" (crash-prone without JIT); add Metal retest note
	* retroarch.cfg: Appendix: Azahar add frame_delay_auto="false",
	  video_threaded="true", audio="64", azahar_use_cpu_jit=disabled,
	  azahar_use_shader_jit=disabled, azahar_is_new_3ds="New 3DS"
	* retroarch.cfg: Checklist: vrr_runloop → OFF; remove Frame Rest;
	  expand per-core overrides for PS1/NDS/Saturn/3DS
	* README.md: Bump version 2.13 → 2.14, rev.12 → rev.13, March → April
	* README.md: §7 Video settings: remove Frame Rest row; update Threaded
	  Video note for per-core usage; Refresh Rate recommend 8192+ frames
	* README.md: §7 Latency: Sync to Exact Content Framerate ON → OFF;
	  Preemptive Frames note disable for Tier 2–3
	* README.md: §7 TV output: rewrite vrr_runloop paragraph (OFF, not ON;
	  explain DRC restoration)
	* README.md: §8 CRT Shaders: restructure preset table by GPU cost tier
	  (Minimal/Low/Medium); add 1080p fallback note for thermal throttling
	* README.md: §10 Tier 1: remove rewind_enable from all cores; add
	  SuperFX overclock per-game for Snes9x; add BRAM per-game for
	  Genesis Plus GX
	* README.md: §10 Tier 2: PS1 add preemptive disabled, threaded video,
	  DRC disabled, duping, audio 48; N64 add threaded video + 3 GLideN64
	  options; NDS run_ahead 1 → 0, add JIT disabled, boot directly,
	  preemptive disabled, frame delay disabled, threaded video, audio 48
	* README.md: §10 Tier 3: Saturn add CD cache, midsync disabled, frame
	  delay disabled, threaded video, audio 64; PPSSPP add texture scaling,
	  frame delay disabled, threaded video, audio 64, fast_memory →
	  disabled + risk note + Metal retest note; Azahar add CPU/shader JIT
	  disabled, New 3DS, frame delay disabled, threaded video, audio 64
	* README.md: §11 Known Issues: update #8 threaded video for per-core
	  usage; add #12 A15 thermal throttling
	* README.md: §12 Checklist: vrr_runloop → OFF; remove Frame Rest;
	  expand per-core overrides for PS1/NDS/Saturn/3DS

